Posts.Content: Sep 29, 2012 03:11AM organa wrote: Because of your age an ultrasound would probably be better.  A mammogram may not show everything because you probably have dense breasts being a young woman.  The lump is most likely not malignant, the odds are in your favor for sure.  The fact that it doesn't hurt doesn't mean much.  Most often breast cancer doesn't hurt.  So don't use that as your basis for not getting any further testing done.  If you didn't get tested and later found out that you did indeed have cancer, how would you feel about not going to the specialist now?
